    "The first is our Modern Transformer, which incorporates all the recent improvements we study and serves as our default transformer model.",
    "The second is our Retro Transformer introduced in Section 3.2, which reverts these modifications.",
    "We also define \"Kaplan\" Transformers to be our Retro Transformer adjusted analytically to approximate Kaplan scaling, representing our ablations as well as suboptimal data scaling.",
    "Modern TransformerWe first standardize our notion of a \"modern\" transformer from which we perform ablations.",
